page.title: 06Home Life,Stickney.
page.content: On Saturday my Dad wakes up at 6 o'clock. He goes to work at 7 o'clock. Just before he goes he wakes my mum up at 6.45am and she puts her washing machine on. Gary my brother gets up at 8 0'clock and puts the video on so that wakes me up.I was going to Sally's for the morning so I caught the 10 0'clock bus to Horbling Lane. She waited for me at the top of the lane .When we got to her house we played records and played on her organ. At 2 0'clock my Dad came and collected us both to go to Skegness. When we got there it was snowing so we came home came again. Dad took Sally home and I watched television until I went to bed at 10 o'clock.
